                                            SUBWAY ENVIRONMENT SIMULATION
                                                  SIMULATION OF
                         SES v4.1 file.  A bidirectional rail tunnel with an open shaft at the middle.
                         A series of trains runs through the tunnel, crossing at different points.
                         This run is intended as a test of the code that calculates annulus volume
                         flows and annulus air velocities around moving trains.
                         The tunnels and routes have a simple gradient profile so we can illustrate
                         the train icons on the profile.
                         Tunnels 101 and 104 have two segments (to check that the correct areas are
                         being accessed).
                         Tunnel 104 is reversed in the route.
                         We have two routes in the tunnel.  Route 1 sends large, long (9.4 m^2, 210 m)
                         in every 50 seconds.  Route 2 sends small, short (8.8 m^2, 130 m) long trains
                         in every 50 seconds, going in the opposite direction.
                                    DESIGN TIME 1700 HRS   JULY       2023
                                                                                             DEVELOPED BY -
                                                                                               PARSONS, BRINCKERHOFF,
                                                                                               QUADE AND DOUGLAS, INC.
                                                                                               NEW YORK CITY, NEW YORK
